# =============================================================================
# File: docker/llama-model/Dockerfile.dockerignore
# Purpose:
#   Restricts the baked-model Docker build context to only files needed for the special GGUF-copy image.
#
# Where this fits in OSAI:
#   Works with docker/llama-model/Dockerfile to avoid accidentally sending unrelated project files to Docker.
#
# Topics to know before editing:
#   Docker/Git ignore patterns and build context hygiene.
#
# Important operational notes:
#   Keep this stricter than normal build context rules because the model image is intentionally large.
# =============================================================================
# Ignore everything by default so the model-image build does not send source,
# secrets, caches, or runtime data to Docker.
*

# Re-include only GGUF model files. This special build context is used only
# when intentionally baking a model into the image.
!models/
!models/*.gguf
